OL,3,C'A scandal': The impact of Taunton
OL,4,CCrown Court closure - as repair costs
OL,5,Cspiral
OL,7,FThe tradition of justice stretches
OL,8,Fback hundreds of years in Taunton. The
OL,9,F'Bloody Assizes', overseen by the
OL,10,Finfamous Judge Jeffreys, were held in
OL,11,Fthe town after the Battle of Sedgemoor
OL,12,Fin 1685. More than 500 people were
OL,13,Ftried in the town after the 'Monmouth
OL,14,FRebellion'. Meanwhile, Britain's
OL,15,Flongest serving prisoner, John
OL,16,FStraffen, was tried at Taunton Assizes
OL,17,Fin 1951. He ended up being behind bars
OL,18,Ffor a record 55 years.
